1
00:00:13,346 --> 00:00:14,973
How's your condition?

2
00:00:18,727 --> 00:00:20,770
So, as always,

3
00:00:21,271 --> 00:00:23,565
your opponent has no idea about this.

4
00:00:23,648 --> 00:00:25,567
He will come at you with full force.

5
00:00:25,650 --> 00:00:28,403
Make sure you don't get caught.

6
00:00:28,486 --> 00:00:30,447
The match is starting soon.

7
00:00:30,947 --> 00:00:32,407
Can we give this a rest?

8
00:00:34,909 --> 00:00:37,287
A loser dog acting all mighty, huh?

9
00:00:44,127 --> 00:00:45,462
I'm counting on you, okay?

10
00:00:54,804 --> 00:00:56,681
That damn bastard.

11
00:01:25,001 --> 00:01:27,295
Good! Let's go!

12
00:01:35,720 --> 00:01:37,806
We've got more power.

13
00:01:37,889 --> 00:01:40,934
Give it your all. Put your soul into it!

14
00:01:41,434 --> 00:01:43,603
Soul? That's so old-fashioned.

15
00:01:48,900 --> 00:01:50,485
Do your best!

16
00:02:06,376 --> 00:02:07,836
<i>I trust you.</i>

17
00:02:07,919 --> 00:02:09,337
Do a good job, okay?

18
00:02:12,715 --> 00:02:15,051
A loser dog acting all mighty, huh?

19
00:02:23,643 --> 00:02:25,145
Johan!

20
00:02:25,937 --> 00:02:27,605
Johan, you did well!

21
00:02:29,482 --> 00:02:32,527
Good job! That was amazing!

22
00:02:32,610 --> 00:02:36,447
<i>You know what'll happen</i>
<i>if you betray me, don't you?</i>

23
00:02:47,167 --> 00:02:52,589
Johan, what are you doing?!
Finish him already!

24
00:03:00,346 --> 00:03:02,140
Move in, Johan!

25
00:03:20,325 --> 00:03:21,659
What's with that guy?

26
00:03:24,120 --> 00:03:25,914
Does he want to end up like me?

27
00:03:37,467 --> 00:03:39,594
Don't run, Hwang Johan!

28
00:04:12,460 --> 00:04:15,004
-I found myself cheering for him.
-Yeah.

29
00:04:27,892 --> 00:04:29,644
Learn how to box!

30
00:04:29,727 --> 00:04:31,813
-Go back to Korea!
-What?

31
00:04:32,522 --> 00:04:34,649
Get out of the ring!

32
00:04:37,277 --> 00:04:38,695
Shut up.

33
00:04:38,778 --> 00:04:39,821
What did you say?

34
00:04:39,904 --> 00:04:41,531
-Come here, you bastard!
-Huh? Sumiko?

35
00:04:41,614 --> 00:04:45,493
-Hey, calm down!
-Who the hell are you? Don't get cocky!

36
00:04:45,576 --> 00:04:46,869
Calm down!

37
00:04:49,580 --> 00:04:53,793
He's just a pitiful guy who doesn't know
a hard worker when he sees one.

38
00:05:01,301 --> 00:05:02,135
Wait, what?

39
00:05:02,927 --> 00:05:03,928
Ryu!

40
00:05:05,346 --> 00:05:06,180
What?

41
00:05:09,600 --> 00:05:11,060
Wait. Stop!

42
00:05:17,650 --> 00:05:18,860
-Sumiko!
-Ryu.

43
00:05:18,943 --> 00:05:19,944
Here.

44
00:05:20,528 --> 00:05:21,529
Thanks.

45
00:05:22,405 --> 00:05:24,198
-Here.
-Oh, thank you.

46
00:05:27,493 --> 00:05:30,371
-Sorry for doing that out of nowhere!
-It's fine.

47
00:05:30,455 --> 00:05:33,333
But wait, do you speak Japanese?

48
00:05:33,916 --> 00:05:35,793
Yes. That's right.

49
00:05:36,836 --> 00:05:40,423
I speak six languages.

50
00:05:41,007 --> 00:05:43,176
Wow, that's incredible.

51
00:05:44,552 --> 00:05:47,263
My name is Sua. Hwang Sua.

52
00:05:48,097 --> 00:05:48,973
Hwang?

53
00:05:49,057 --> 00:05:51,726
Yes. I'm Johan's little sister.

54
00:05:52,477 --> 00:05:53,770
What is your name?

55
00:05:53,853 --> 00:05:56,981
I'm Sumiko.

56
00:05:57,065 --> 00:05:58,566
Oh, Sumiko.

57
00:05:58,649 --> 00:06:03,112
Thank you so much for helping me, Sumiko.

58
00:06:03,196 --> 00:06:06,574
Also, I'm sorry.

59
00:06:07,367 --> 00:06:11,579
When I get angry, I get tunnel vision.

60
00:06:12,663 --> 00:06:14,665
I'm so sorry.

61
00:06:14,749 --> 00:06:15,792
It's fine.

62
00:06:15,875 --> 00:06:18,753
Though, it did catch us by surprise.

63
00:06:18,836 --> 00:06:21,297
-Right?
-Yeah.

64
00:06:26,010 --> 00:06:30,348
Could it be that you two are

65
00:06:30,848 --> 00:06:34,185
my brother's fans?

66
00:06:45,405 --> 00:06:46,697
Mr. Shim.

67
00:06:47,198 --> 00:06:50,284
I'm sorry we couldn't deliver results
after being given the chance

68
00:06:50,368 --> 00:06:52,412
to compete in an international match.

69
00:06:52,912 --> 00:06:56,958
No, Johan fought with everything he had.

70
00:06:58,376 --> 00:07:01,003
Could I chat with him alone?

71
00:07:01,087 --> 00:07:03,798
Oh, yes, go right ahead.

72
00:07:06,467 --> 00:07:09,762
Make sure you thank him properly.

73
00:07:11,889 --> 00:07:13,641
Let's go.

74
00:07:39,375 --> 00:07:42,295
Don't put me on edge like that.

75
00:07:43,963 --> 00:07:46,549
Who told you
to let it drag out to a decision?

76
00:07:47,049 --> 00:07:49,051
You just needed to give us a clean loss.

77
00:07:52,054 --> 00:07:55,391
A knockout. I meant a knockout.

78
00:07:57,143 --> 00:08:00,938
Well, fine.
As promised, you became a loser dog.

79
00:08:01,606 --> 00:08:03,483
So I'll keep my promise too.

80
00:08:22,293 --> 00:08:24,754
It's because you keep reading
this kind of trash.

81
00:08:35,890 --> 00:08:37,099
See you again.

82
00:08:53,783 --> 00:08:55,284
Johan!

83
00:08:57,620 --> 00:09:00,039
Johan! Oh, no!

84
00:09:00,122 --> 00:09:02,875
Are you okay? That looks painful.

85
00:09:04,377 --> 00:09:05,253
Huh?

86
00:09:05,336 --> 00:09:06,796
Hmm? Oh!

87
00:09:07,505 --> 00:09:09,048
Good work.

88
00:09:11,717 --> 00:09:13,094
Why's that guy here?

89
00:09:16,556 --> 00:09:19,725
These two were really cheering you on.

90
00:09:20,601 --> 00:09:21,894
Isn't that right?

91
00:09:21,978 --> 00:09:25,356
Uh, sorry, I don't know any Korean.

92
00:09:25,439 --> 00:09:27,900
Oh, that's right.

93
00:09:28,568 --> 00:09:29,443
Huh?

94
00:09:30,152 --> 00:09:33,155
You're friends with Johan,
aren't you, Ryu?

95
00:09:33,781 --> 00:09:35,157
Friends?

96
00:09:35,241 --> 00:09:37,118
Wait, no. I didn't say anything.

97
00:09:37,618 --> 00:09:39,829
What? Don't be shy!

98
00:09:40,329 --> 00:09:41,539
Oh, Johan.

99
00:09:42,039 --> 00:09:48,713
Ryu asked me how to say
"Good work" in Korean before you got here.

100
00:09:48,796 --> 00:09:53,759
Oh, my gosh! I'm so jealous.
You have such a nice friend.

101
00:09:54,260 --> 00:09:57,221
I'm gonna hang out with Sumiko.

102
00:09:57,305 --> 00:09:58,514
Move over.

103
00:09:58,598 --> 00:10:00,099
Sumiko, let's go!

104
00:10:00,182 --> 00:10:01,934
-Huh? Wait--
-Hurry!

105
00:10:02,018 --> 00:10:03,060
Ryu!

106
00:10:04,437 --> 00:10:05,521
<i>Oh!</i>

107
00:10:06,105 --> 00:10:08,441
So, you're the one
who ran from the hospital.

108
00:10:09,900 --> 00:10:11,402
I didn't run.

109
00:10:11,485 --> 00:10:12,445
The hospital?

110
00:10:13,404 --> 00:10:17,450
Thank you so much for saving Ryu.

111
00:10:19,243 --> 00:10:20,369
It was nothing.

112
00:10:27,918 --> 00:10:30,671
-What? Did you hurt your hand?
-Nah.

113
00:10:31,297 --> 00:10:33,424
It's just a bit numb. I'm fine.

114
00:10:33,924 --> 00:10:37,928
You gotta watch out
for punch-drunk syndrome and stuff.

115
00:10:38,012 --> 00:10:39,764
Please be more careful!

116
00:10:39,847 --> 00:10:41,349
You've got some on you again.

117
00:10:41,432 --> 00:10:43,351
I'm fine. Don't worry.

118
00:10:43,434 --> 00:10:45,728
I usually take my opponent down
before they hit me.

119
00:10:45,811 --> 00:10:46,979
Huh?

120
00:10:48,022 --> 00:10:52,068
Oh, right. You did great, Johan.
You win some, you lose some.

121
00:10:52,693 --> 00:10:53,944
That's just how it goes.

122
00:10:54,028 --> 00:10:55,863
-Keep it up!
-Eat your food.

123
00:10:55,946 --> 00:10:57,365
You two are really close.

124
00:10:58,366 --> 00:11:00,743
It's always been just the two of us.

125
00:11:02,203 --> 00:11:03,037
What?

126
00:11:03,120 --> 00:11:04,872
Don't run your mouth off.

127
00:11:07,208 --> 00:11:10,211
So, are you two a couple?

128
00:11:11,003 --> 00:11:12,088
No.

129
00:11:12,171 --> 00:11:16,926
Ryu is just staying at my place
while he's here on vacation.

130
00:11:17,802 --> 00:11:21,013
-Oh, is that so?
-It's true.

131
00:11:21,097 --> 00:11:23,891
We're just childhood friends. Right?

132
00:11:24,392 --> 00:11:25,518
Yeah.

133
00:11:25,601 --> 00:11:26,936
"Childhood friends"?

134
00:11:27,019 --> 00:11:28,771
Yeah. You see…

135
00:11:28,854 --> 00:11:31,357
I had a lot going on at home.

136
00:11:31,440 --> 00:11:36,362
So, ever since elementary school,
Ryu's family has done so much for me.

137
00:11:37,488 --> 00:11:39,240
Since elementary school?

138
00:11:40,116 --> 00:11:42,118
You've known each other for a long time.

139
00:11:43,244 --> 00:11:46,914
But what is a "childhood friend"?

140
00:11:48,457 --> 00:11:50,918
How is it different from being a couple?

141
00:11:51,001 --> 00:11:52,420
-Hwang Sua.
-Huh?

142
00:11:52,503 --> 00:11:53,796
That's private.

143
00:11:54,630 --> 00:11:56,882
I'm so sorry! Oh, I did it again.

144
00:11:58,134 --> 00:12:02,221
No, it's totally fine.
Let's just forget privacy altogether.

145
00:12:04,306 --> 00:12:05,349
So heavy…

146
00:12:07,643 --> 00:12:09,270
He's a lightweight, huh?

147
00:12:10,229 --> 00:12:12,648
Yeah, but he still drinks.

148
00:12:17,194 --> 00:12:18,320
Walk properly.

149
00:12:18,821 --> 00:12:21,532
<i>The church remained largely undamaged.</i>

150
00:12:21,615 --> 00:12:27,037
<i>As there is still smoke, we advise locals</i>
<i>to keep doors and windows closed.</i>

151
00:12:27,121 --> 00:12:32,418
<i>Our team found a Molotov cocktail</i>
<i>near the altar while on-site</i>

152
00:12:32,501 --> 00:12:34,503
<i>that may have caused the fire.</i>

153
00:12:35,045 --> 00:12:38,215
<i>Meanwhile, a minor has turned himself in</i>
<i>to the police today.</i>

154
00:12:38,299 --> 00:12:42,303
<i>-The motive remains unclear.</i>
-The culprit was a kid, huh?

155
00:12:42,386 --> 00:12:43,763
<i>Investigation is ongoing.</i>

156
00:12:46,640 --> 00:12:51,520
This is amazing, Sumiko.
Did you draw all this yourself?

157
00:12:51,604 --> 00:12:52,605
Yeah.

158
00:12:53,647 --> 00:12:55,900
How long have you been in Berlin?

159
00:12:56,734 --> 00:12:59,612
Well, I guess this is my third year.

160
00:13:00,613 --> 00:13:05,117
She works part-time
to put herself through fashion college.

161
00:13:05,951 --> 00:13:08,954
-That's so cool.
-No, not at all.

162
00:13:09,038 --> 00:13:12,666
I do work part-time,
but I'm also in debt to my dad.

163
00:13:12,750 --> 00:13:14,251
It's still amazing.

164
00:13:15,753 --> 00:13:19,298
What about you, Sua?
You're a student, right?

165
00:13:19,381 --> 00:13:22,968
Yeah. I go to Heidelberg University.

166
00:13:23,844 --> 00:13:24,845
What?

167
00:13:25,763 --> 00:13:29,099
Huh? Which department?

168
00:13:32,394 --> 00:13:34,980
Medical. Is it medicine in Japanese?

169
00:13:35,064 --> 00:13:38,776
-Wow, that's seriously impressive.
-Amazing!

170
00:13:38,859 --> 00:13:40,319
Not at all.

171
00:13:41,445 --> 00:13:45,366
Johan is way more amazing than me.

172
00:13:47,618 --> 00:13:53,290
Because I happened to be good at studying,
Johan has always supported me.

173
00:13:54,542 --> 00:13:57,169
He's been working hard to earn money

174
00:13:57,670 --> 00:14:03,384
and provide me with a good environment.

175
00:14:04,426 --> 00:14:05,261
I see.

176
00:14:09,306 --> 00:14:12,017
We don't have parents.

177
00:14:13,853 --> 00:14:16,438
Johan is my mom and dad.

178
00:14:16,522 --> 00:14:19,024
He's my entire family.

179
00:14:21,569 --> 00:14:24,154
If I were ordinary,

180
00:14:25,614 --> 00:14:30,619
he might not have had to

181
00:14:31,120 --> 00:14:33,414
push himself so hard.

182
00:14:37,918 --> 00:14:40,838
I wonder if he is happy.

183
00:15:14,121 --> 00:15:15,956
-Yo.
-Hey.

184
00:15:28,177 --> 00:15:29,261
Um…

185
00:15:30,763 --> 00:15:32,806
Is your hand…

186
00:15:34,308 --> 00:15:35,309
Oh.

187
00:15:35,976 --> 00:15:37,269
It's nothing.

188
00:15:41,732 --> 00:15:45,069
Your match was amazing.

189
00:15:46,070 --> 00:15:48,697
It was my first time seeing boxing live.

190
00:15:49,198 --> 00:15:50,532
How do I put this?

191
00:15:51,575 --> 00:15:52,868
It was moving.

192
00:15:55,245 --> 00:15:56,455
How?

193
00:15:57,164 --> 00:16:00,417
Even when you fell, you got back up.

194
00:16:02,628 --> 00:16:03,629
What?

195
00:16:04,588 --> 00:16:07,091
Uh, basically…

196
00:16:08,592 --> 00:16:10,511
The way you never gave up

197
00:16:11,720 --> 00:16:14,598
made you look stronger than anyone else.

198
00:16:29,279 --> 00:16:33,117
Why didn't you say anything to the police?

199
00:16:34,994 --> 00:16:37,121
The one who set the church on fire

200
00:16:37,204 --> 00:16:39,081
was a kid, right?

201
00:16:41,709 --> 00:16:43,627
It was on the news earlier.

202
00:16:49,341 --> 00:16:52,177
The kid had the same eyes

203
00:16:52,803 --> 00:16:54,054
as me.

204
00:16:55,055 --> 00:16:56,056
Eyes?

205
00:16:57,307 --> 00:16:58,851
Hmm.

206
00:17:03,063 --> 00:17:05,107
When you feel like…

207
00:17:07,484 --> 00:17:13,240
no one in the world sees you…

208
00:17:16,326 --> 00:17:18,328
it makes you…

209
00:17:21,457 --> 00:17:24,918
want to destroy…

210
00:17:27,421 --> 00:17:28,380
that world.

211
00:17:37,431 --> 00:17:39,141
What am I even saying?

212
00:18:27,898 --> 00:18:30,734
NEW MESSAGE FROM SUA

213
00:18:30,818 --> 00:18:32,444
THANKS TO YOU, I'M HAPPY.

214
00:18:32,528 --> 00:18:34,780
I'M OKAY NOW.
I'M GLAD YOU MADE A GOOD FRIEND.

215
00:18:36,198 --> 00:18:37,407
What is she saying?

216
00:18:53,173 --> 00:18:54,049
Good morning.

217
00:18:54,133 --> 00:18:55,259
Hey.

218
00:18:56,176 --> 00:18:57,177
Here.

219
00:19:03,684 --> 00:19:06,436
What are your plans for today?

220
00:19:07,729 --> 00:19:09,231
Nothing really.

221
00:19:12,317 --> 00:19:13,318
Then…

222
00:19:16,071 --> 00:19:17,322
come with me.

223
00:19:18,323 --> 00:19:20,492
Huh? Where to?

224
00:19:23,453 --> 00:19:26,832
I'll show you something interesting.

225
00:19:28,000 --> 00:19:28,834
What is it?

226
00:19:32,838 --> 00:19:33,839
The soul.

227
00:19:35,299 --> 00:19:36,466
The soul?

228
00:19:40,554 --> 00:19:41,430
Hello?

229
00:19:41,513 --> 00:19:43,473
<i>Where the hell are you, Johan?</i>

230
00:19:43,557 --> 00:19:45,601
Sorry, I have some business
to take care of.

231
00:19:45,684 --> 00:19:49,062
<i>What kind of business</i>
<i>could you have in Germany?</i>

232
00:19:50,647 --> 00:19:53,317
<i>Whatever. Where are you right now?</i>

233
00:19:53,400 --> 00:19:55,986
<i>Mr. Shim wants to see you</i>
<i>before heading back to Korea.</i>

234
00:19:56,069 --> 00:19:59,656
That's perfect.
I have something to discuss with him too.

235
00:20:00,741 --> 00:20:04,620
<i>You're not gonna say</i>
<i>something unnecessary again, are you?</i>

236
00:20:05,120 --> 00:20:07,456
-It's something important.
-<i>Hey, you--</i>

237
00:20:28,477 --> 00:20:29,561
Johan.

238
00:20:41,865 --> 00:20:43,325
I'm not doing this anymore.

239
00:20:44,534 --> 00:20:45,535
What?

240
00:20:49,039 --> 00:20:51,333
I'm saying I'm not gonna do

241
00:20:52,501 --> 00:20:54,211
these fixed fights anymore.

242
00:20:54,753 --> 00:20:55,879
Mr. Shim.

243
00:20:56,588 --> 00:20:57,839
Could it be that you…

244
00:20:57,923 --> 00:21:00,092
No. I'm just doing my job as a promoter.

245
00:21:03,512 --> 00:21:04,805
What nonsense is this?

246
00:21:04,888 --> 00:21:06,181
And also,

247
00:21:07,099 --> 00:21:09,017
I'm not a loser.

248
00:21:10,936 --> 00:21:12,854
I'm not a loser dog!

249
00:21:17,943 --> 00:21:19,903
You bastard. What's your problem?!

250
00:21:23,282 --> 00:21:24,241
You damn bastard.

251
00:21:24,324 --> 00:21:25,742
Oh, my bag!

252
00:21:59,860 --> 00:22:01,695
Yes! I totally did it.

253
00:22:03,989 --> 00:22:07,451
You're seriously crazy, you know that?

254
00:22:07,534 --> 00:22:09,411
Wait, I'm not in trouble, am I?

255
00:22:09,995 --> 00:22:12,331
-I sent that guy flying.
-It's okay.

256
00:22:12,414 --> 00:22:13,415
I'll be okay, right?

257
00:22:14,666 --> 00:22:16,168
Up until now,

258
00:22:17,836 --> 00:22:19,880
I'd been losing matches on purpose.

259
00:22:21,173 --> 00:22:25,927
Then that man would give me money.

260
00:22:26,595 --> 00:22:27,596
What?

261
00:22:28,597 --> 00:22:32,059
-But you…
-Yeah?

262
00:22:32,142 --> 00:22:33,810
You sent him flying.

263
00:22:35,562 --> 00:22:36,563
So, now…

264
00:22:37,773 --> 00:22:39,274
I'm free!

265
00:22:39,358 --> 00:22:40,609
Freedom!

266
00:22:48,450 --> 00:22:50,285
To be honest, this injury…

267
00:22:53,914 --> 00:22:58,377
I got it when I saved you.

268
00:22:59,211 --> 00:23:00,879
So, it was my fault?

269
00:23:00,962 --> 00:23:03,048
No, it wasn't.

270
00:23:04,341 --> 00:23:06,968
It's thanks to you.

271
00:23:08,678 --> 00:23:09,679
This…

272
00:23:12,182 --> 00:23:13,850
This is the mark of freedom.

273
00:23:18,021 --> 00:23:19,773
Can you survive from now on?

274
00:23:22,067 --> 00:23:25,278
I was already dead.

275
00:23:56,393 --> 00:23:58,311
I used to read this.

276
00:24:01,648 --> 00:24:03,442
It's a masterpiece.

277
00:24:05,235 --> 00:24:07,237
Is this how you learned Japanese?

278
00:24:14,244 --> 00:24:16,580
I've read this many times.

279
00:24:16,663 --> 00:24:17,998
Over and over.

280
00:24:21,418 --> 00:24:25,589
Because I wanted to understand

281
00:24:27,507 --> 00:24:30,427
the meaning behind the story.

282
00:24:31,761 --> 00:24:33,054
Impressive.

283
00:24:34,473 --> 00:24:35,599
Impressive, right?

284
00:24:36,099 --> 00:24:37,017
Yeah.

285
00:24:48,028 --> 00:24:50,697
What will you do now?

286
00:24:55,202 --> 00:24:58,079
I'll go back to Korea.

287
00:25:00,540 --> 00:25:01,791
I see.

288
00:25:02,459 --> 00:25:03,668
And after that?

289
00:25:09,382 --> 00:25:10,884
After that?

290
00:25:13,595 --> 00:25:14,930
How would I know?

291
00:25:17,182 --> 00:25:18,225
Right.

292
00:25:20,310 --> 00:25:21,937
From here on out…

293
00:25:25,315 --> 00:25:26,942
it's my story.

294
00:25:39,663 --> 00:25:40,664
Huh?

295
00:26:28,169 --> 00:26:29,296
What about you?

296
00:26:29,796 --> 00:26:30,797
Me?

297
00:26:33,633 --> 00:26:34,843
Are you

298
00:26:36,219 --> 00:26:38,680
still gonna stay here?

299
00:26:43,643 --> 00:26:46,438
I'll head back too.

300
00:26:50,650 --> 00:26:54,195
I've decided to go back.

301
00:26:58,450 --> 00:26:59,451
I see.

302
00:27:00,869 --> 00:27:01,870
Yeah.

303
00:27:05,874 --> 00:27:07,584
I don't really get it myself.

304
00:27:08,960 --> 00:27:10,587
But watching you,

305
00:27:11,338 --> 00:27:16,092
it felt like you won
something more important

306
00:27:16,176 --> 00:27:17,927
even though you lost the match.

307
00:27:24,100 --> 00:27:25,101
All this time…

308
00:27:27,395 --> 00:27:28,897
I've been running away…

309
00:27:31,816 --> 00:27:34,235
from things I didn't know how to handle.

310
00:27:36,529 --> 00:27:37,530
But…

311
00:27:40,533 --> 00:27:41,534
I also…

312
00:27:43,495 --> 00:27:44,579
Me too.

313
00:27:52,504 --> 00:27:54,798
I'm just like you.

314
00:27:56,132 --> 00:27:57,133
What?

315
00:27:59,094 --> 00:28:02,263
That's why I was at the church.

316
00:28:05,058 --> 00:28:06,101
Because…

317
00:28:12,107 --> 00:28:17,862
I was lying to myself.

318
00:28:21,866 --> 00:28:27,497
<i>Caution. The train is now arriving.</i>

319
00:28:28,581 --> 00:28:29,582
But…

320
00:28:31,876 --> 00:28:33,086
I'm not anymore.

321
00:28:40,093 --> 00:28:41,302
How about you?

322
00:28:43,972 --> 00:28:45,223
Can you win?

323
00:28:53,022 --> 00:28:54,149
I'll give it a try.

324
00:29:07,454 --> 00:29:08,580
Bye, then.

325
00:29:09,414 --> 00:29:10,415
Bye.

326
00:29:19,132 --> 00:29:24,471
<i>Hello, welcome aboard</i>
<i>the local train to Schönefeld.</i>

327
00:29:24,554 --> 00:29:27,223
<i>We will be departing shortly.</i>

328
00:29:27,307 --> 00:29:32,395
<i>All of us at the German Railway</i>
<i>wish you a pleasant journey.</i>

329
00:30:25,198 --> 00:30:28,409
JOHAN

330
00:32:47,256 --> 00:32:50,176
Subtitle translation by: Remi Miura
